org.ow2.proactive.resourcemanager.common.event

Class RMInitialState

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ow2.proactive.resourcemanager.common.event.RMInitialState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    @PublicAPI
public class RMInitialState
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Defines a state of the Resource Manager for a Monitor. In order to receive Resource Manager events, a monitor register itself to RMMonitoring by the method RMMonitoring.addRMEventListener(RMEventListener listener, RMEventType... events), and get an initial state which is the snapshot of Resource Manager state, with its nodes and NodeSources.
    Since:
    ProActive Scheduling 0.9
    See Also:
    RMNodeEvent, RMNodeSourceEvent, RMMonitoring, Serialized Form

      • cloneAndFilter

        public RMStateDelta cloneAndFilter(long counterKnownByClient)
        Clones current state events, but keep only those events which has counter bigger than provided 'filter' Event counter can take values [0, +). So if filter is '-1' then all events will returned.
        Parameters:
        counterKnownByClient - latest counter associated with event known by client
        Returns:
        RMStateDelta where all the events bigger than 'filter'

      • cloneAndFilterNotRemovedOnly

        public RMStateFull cloneAndFilterNotRemovedOnly()
        Clones current state events, but keep only those events which was not removed.
        Returns:
        RMStateFull where all the events are correspond to existing node/nodesources
